## Installation

### Option A: Automatic (Recommended)

Run this to install the dependency and automatically save the hash:

```bash
zig fetch --save https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/updater.zig/archive/refs/tags/0.0.1.tar.gz
```

After running, Zig updates your `build.zig.zon` with something like:

```zig
.dependencies = .{
    .updater = .{
        .url = "https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/updater.zig/archive/refs/tags/0.0.1.tar.gz",
        .hash = "updater-0.0.1-TGNPfI71AQC5tZYKfmrg9jnF-h0acMF4OuIL3AgIcKq0",
    },
},
```

Then in your `build.zig`:

```zig
const updater_dep = b.dependency("updater", .{
    .target = target,
    .optimize = optimize,
});
exe.root_module.addImport("updater", updater_dep.module("updater"));
```

### Option B: Manual

```bash
zig fetch --hash https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/updater.zig/archive/refs/tags/0.0.1.tar.gz
```

Copy that hash into:

```zig
.hash = "<your_hash_here>" // which is updater-0.0.1-TGNPfI71AQC5tZYKfmrg9jnF-h0acMF4OuIL3AgIcKq0
```

## Quick Start

```zig
const std = @import("std");
const updater = @import("updater");

pub fn main() !void {
    var gpa = std.heap.GeneralPurposeAllocator(.{}){};
    defer _ = gpa.deinit();
    const allocator = gpa.allocator();

    const result = try updater.checkGitHub(
        allocator,
        "muhammad-fiaz",
        "updater.zig",
        "1.0.0",
    );

    if (result.has_update) {
        std.debug.print("Update available: {s}\n", .{result.latest_version.?});
    }
}
```

